The paper deals with security and privacy in cryptographic protocols, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The Stash Shuffle is a data structure used in algorithms for sorting and searching, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory and coding, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The Stash Shuffle can be used in distributed systems, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper involves machine learning and statistical analysis, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
